{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}Hello HomepageController!{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
<style>
    .example-wrapper { margin: 1em auto; max-width: 800px; width: 95%; font: 18px/1.5 sans-serif; }
    .example-wrapper code { background: #F5F5F5; padding: 2px 6px; }
</style>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="col-6 mx-auto mt-4 px-5 pb-4 index border">
        

            <div class="row mt-3">
                In this web application you can create a random list of dishes and create a shopping list. To do this:
            </div>
            <div class="row mt-3">
                1. Create an account/log in.
            </div>
            <div class="row mt-3">
                2. Create new dishes in the "dishes" tab.
            </div>
            <div class="row mt-3">
                3. For each dish you can add ingredients and the amount required to prepare the dish. 
            </div>
            <div class="row mt-3">
                4. After creating dishes, assigning ingredients and setting type of meal, generate spreadsheet. Choose the number of days and for how many days you need to create a shopping list.
            </div>
            <div class="row mt-3">
                After completing these steps, an excel file will be generated which will contain a randomly generated menu and a shopping list summed according to the number of days selected by the user.
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>

{% endblock %}
